    "cards": [
        {
            "time": "3-5 Minutes", 
            "level": "Introduction |", 
            "headline": "Compose with a Grid", 
            "exampleMediaPath": "1.jpg", 
            "type": "IntroCard", 
            "id": "intro_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Using a grid to compose photos is the most basic concept a photographer needs to understand. This lesson will teach you to look at your photo as a grid.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "header": "Next", 
            "text": "Start", 
            "type": "ButtonCard", 
            "id": "milestone_start", 
            "icon": "down"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think of your photo as if it is made up of nine equal rectangles. Strong visuals use all the rectangles in the grid to tell the story.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_1", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "2.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Placing the grid on this photo divides one image into nine equal rectangles.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "2.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Most smartphones allow you to display a grid in your camera app. Use the grid when doing the activity.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_2", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "3.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Do not place your subject in the middle with no thought to the rest of the grid.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "3.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The grid is intended to do more than do more than center your photos. Let\u2019s look at how the lines of the grid help us compose better photos.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_3", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "4.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "This line defines the bottom third of the frame.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "4.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the photo is a landscape, this line is often used to establish the horizon in a grid.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_4", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "5.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "This line defines the top third of the frame.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "5.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the photo is a portrait, the subject's eyes are usually placed on the top horizontal line. As you practice this more you may find that sometimes the bottom line works better.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_5", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "6.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "The grid allows you to arrange complex images in a single frame.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "6.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To use a grid most effectively, the vertical and horizontal lines should work together to define the frame.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_6", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Clearly define the edges of your frame. Try to have important shapes complete within the frame.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_7", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "7.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo the important elements complete within the frame.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "7.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Remember to fill the entire frame with visual information. Use the grid to organize that information and create more compelling photos.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_8", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "1.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": "\u00a9"
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Here the grid organizes the visual information in a compelling way.", 
            "references": [
                "compose_with_a_grid::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "1.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_6"
        }, 
